For instance:
```
maxaggregate([(&#39;Kohli&#39;,73),(&#39;Ashwin&#39;,33),(&#39;Kohli&#39;,7),(&#39;Pujara&#39;,122),(&#39;Ashwin&#39;,90)]) 
```
should return:
```
[&#39;Ashwin&#39;]
```
because the aggregate score of Kolhi is 80, of Ashwin is 123 and of Pujara is 122, of which 123 is the highest.

```
def maxaggregate(l):
  d = {}
  for i in l:
    if i[0] in d:
      d[i[0]] += i[1]
    else:
      d[i[0]] = i[1]
  m = max(list(d.values()))
  x = []
  for i in d:
    if d[i] == m:
      x.append(i)
  return sorted(x)
```

